description: Reprints political cartoons, Joe Bob Briggs and Ian Shoales columns, and comic strips: Calvin & Hobbes, The Far Side, Outland, Doonesbury, Angriest Dog in the World (David Lynch), and Life In Hell (Matt Groening)

Volume 1, Number Six.

Published weekly by Jerome Sinkovec at Menomonee Falls,Wisconsin, 53051.

The Golden Fleece

name: X-Treme X-Men Tormenta : Arena

description: Collects : X-Treme X-Men Annual 2001
name: X-Treme X-Men Especial 2003

description: Collects : X-Treme X-Men : Savage Land (2001) #01 to 04
name: X-Treme X-Men: Tierra Salvaje

description: Collects : Generation X San Diego Con Edition - Classic X-Men Vol.1 #1 (2ª S.) - Marvel Fanfare Vol.1 #40 (2ª S.) - Bizarre Adventures Vol.1 #27 (2ª S.) - Amazing Adult Fantasy Vol.1 #14 (2ª S.)
name: X-Men : Rarezas

description: Collecting the 6-issue miniseries written by horror master Niles (30 Days of Night)! TV pundit Jack Ryder is transformed him into the Creeper, a superhuman with incredible strength, agility, stamina and an enhanced healing factor. Ryder dispatches his opponents and now calls forth his bestial alter ego in Gotham's war on crime.
name: TPB

description:
Storm clouds gather over Westeros in the fifth installment of Daniel Abraham's gripping adaptation of George R. R. Martin's fantasy masterpiece A Game of Thrones. A childish game gone horribly wrong pits Arya Stark against Prince Joffrey, with Sansa Stark in the middle. But behind youthful rivalries, cold-blooded political intrigue is at work as Queen Cersei uses all her wiles to blunt the influence of Eddard Stark, the Hand of the King. Meanwhile, Lady Catelyn has journeyed to King's Landing with the blade used in the attempted assassination of her son Bran-evidence that will upset a precarious balance of power. And in Winterfell, a dying Bran takes a mystical journey . . . and faces a fateful choice.

Sansa Stark gets a glimpse of her betrothed's true nature, while Catelyn Stark arrives in King's Landing, and Bran Stark has strange dreams.

volume.name: George R.R. Martin's A Game of Thrones

description: As Britt Reid fights to live up to the legacy of The Green Hornet, will he ruin his father's other legacy? The newspaper industry's plight hits the Daily Sentinel, and a harsh round of layoffs puts Britt on edge. As the elder Kato helps him grasp a problem he can't beat with his fists, Britt's frustration drives him to shocking brutality in a search for the source of a human-trafficking ring. Written by newspaper veteran Mark Rahner (The Seattle Times, "Rotten").
name: Deadline Pressure

description: When Miriya's veritech crashes, Max goes after her and has to face four Invid Hellcats. Meanwhile, the plan to use Tesla to rescue Rick, Lisa, Karen, Kami and Rem from the Invid Hive begins.
name: Unto the Breach!

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: The rescue operation leads some of the Sentinels deeper into the Invid Hive and all goes well but then they learn that Rick, Lisa, Karen, Kami and Rem have been scheduled for dissection.
name: Where Humans Dare!

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: The battle to free Garuda from Invid tyranny continues on the planet and the Garudans join in but are they in time to save Rick, Lisa and Karen.
name: A Portion for Foxes

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: After exposure to the deadly Garuda atmosphere, Rick, Lisa and Karen are in a lethal altered state of consciousness. The Garudans attempt to go into the trio's dream realms of their minds and heal them.
name: Garudans in the Mist

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: Back in Tirol space, the council has put Edwards in charge of the Fantoma mining operations and Breetai willingly transfers his command to Edwards and the mining continues. But Breetai has a plan to foil Edwards.
name: To Walk...Among Giants

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description:
Rem is delivered to Haydon IV where the Regis interrogates him and probes his mind hoping to find out the secrets of the Protoculture Matrix.

Note: Issue also has an interview with Carl Macek, one of the creators of the Robotech cartoon series.
name: Destination Earth

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: Minmei flees when Edwards is given full authorization to pursue the Zentraedi, the Invid Regent arrives on Haydon IV but his wife is gone and Rem is there, and then the Sentinels arrive.
name: The Predator and Prey

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: The Sentinels come up with a plan to get medical treatment for Rick, Lisa, Karen and Miriya on Haydon IV and Tesla undergoes a startling transformation.
name: A Clockwork Planet

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book III

description: This issue features a timeline and summary of the events that occurred in the entire Robotech saga, from Zor's birth, through the Macross, Sentinels, Masters and New Generations sagas to the search for the lost SDF-3.
name: Special Zero Edition

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: While Vince Grant and his group take ill comrades Rick, Lisa, Karen and Miriya to Haydon IV and the Invid Regent, Jack and Janice and company in veritechs above the planet have to deal with powerful foes. Meanwhile, Minmei, with the help of a stranger, continues in her escape.
name: World Killers

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: Edwards has ordered pursuit and capture of the escaping Minmei and her mysterious benefactor and Breetai and his Zentraedi fleet. Meanwhile, on Haydon IV, the negotiations with the Invid Regent continue, Rick, Lisa, Karen and Miriya receive medical treatment, and Jack and Janice and company continue to deal with the Haydon IV defense systems.
name: No Man's Land

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: Jack and Janice and company figure out how to avoid Haydon IV's defense systems but then Janice disappears. Rick, Lisa, Karen and Miriya are cured but have some unusual side effects. And Breetai has some tricks up his sleeve for the forces attacking his fleet while Minmei is forced back into Edwards' clutches.
name: Specters in Midnight

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: With Minmei now a hostage of Edwards, Dr. Lang secretly orders a rescue operation; the Sentinels attempt their prisoner exchange with the Invid Regent; and Jack and company continue to search for Janice under the surface of Haydon IV.
name: Prisoner of Fate

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: Under the surface of Haydon IV, Janice undergoes a transformation and reveals her true identity to Jack and company and then leads them on a mission to the planet's awareness; Tesla causes problems in the prisoner exchange which brings Rick Hunter and the others back into the Invid Regent's clutches.
name: Monkey Wrench

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: Rick Hunter and company initiate a daring plan to free the Praxians from the Invid's clutches and under the planet's surface, Janice, now in robotic form, tries to link with the planet's awareness in order to gain control of the planet's systems and Tesla gains entry into an Invid hive with the intent to fulfill his destiny.
name: Clockwork of Doom

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: Tesla gains a new form and new powers and has plans for his destiny. Meanwhile, surrounded and seemingly trapped in the detention center, Rick Hunter and company battle the Invid.
name: Seraphim Avenging

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: Vowad realizes his mistake and the result is not good for the Invid; Tesla is recaptured and tries to convince the Sentinels that he can help them; Breetai and his troops arrive and inform the Sentinels of General Edwards' treachery back on the SDF-3.
name: Conquer and Divine

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: As Dr. Lang sends a crew to try to beat the Robotech Masters to Earth, the Sentinels divide forces and go on different paths to stop both the Invid and General Edwards. The Sentinels also learn more about the Genesis Pit and Zor.
name: Disparate Path

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: On their new ship, the Ark Angel, the Sentinels go against the Invid Regent's new and deadly soldiers, the Black Death Destroyers. Meanwhile back on Tirol, Lieutenant Nicks gets some unexpected help in her efforts to locate Lynn Minmei who has been imprisoned by General Edwards.
name: Dance with the Devil

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: Jonathan Wolf, Vince Grant and Breetai have returned to Tirol to try to stop General Edwards' growing control and face trial for accusations of treason, conspiracy, murder and theft; Dr. Lang and Edwards have a private meeting in which both reveal surprises; and the Sentinels, on board the Ark Angel, make plans to free Spheris but discover that they cannot use their weapons.
name: Summit

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: The Sentinels use a daring plan that involves Tesla in order to try to free Spheris; on Tirol, Lieutenant Nicks and a mysterious man try to find and free Lynn Minmei while the trial of Breetai, Wolf and Grant continues and then turns against General Edwards.
name: Checkmate

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: General Edwards' true nature and intentions are finally known to all and as the net tightens around him, he unveils some surprises that he hopes will enable him to escape with Lynn Minmei. And on Spheris, the Sentinels' plan to free the planet goes well – for a while.
name: Requiem for Justice

volume.name: Robotech II: The Sentinels - Book IV

description: Betty's sprained ankle looks to put a kink in her ski trip with the Veronica and Nancy! Not prepared to leave their friend out of the mix, the girls bring her along unaware that Betty's injury may turn out to be the best thing that could have happened to her!
name: Trip Slip-Up / Best Friends

volume.name: New Kids On The Block Comics Tour '90/91

description:
Led by the Brave One, the cats return to the surface world and commence their long-overdue naps. James, trapped overnight in the (most likely haunted) graveyard by his inability to scale fences, is witness to a horrible baby-knapping/eating ring led by a mysterious goat-headed creature.

Creators Jennifer Feinberg and Todd Meister

volume.name: Felix the Cat’s Blockbuster Movie Bonanza

name: The Tower of Sheba and Attack of the Great Apes

volume.name: Edgar Rice Burroughs Tarzan of the Apes

description:
Featuring work from some of the most prominent names in comics including Dave Gibbons and Grant Morrison, follow along as the Doctor plays out his classic tales, all featuring state-of-the-art coloring by Charlie Kirchoff. Stories collected include "City of the Damned," "Dreamers of Death," "Iron Legion," "Spider-God," "Changes," and more!

Collects Doctor Who Classics Vol. 1-3

1. Wonder Wart-Hog Meets Super-Fool

2. Wonder Wart-Hog Goes A Freedom-Riding

3. Wonder Wart-Hog Encounters Super Granny

4. Wonder Wart-Hog And The Return Of The Masked Meanie

5. Wonder Wart-Hog And The Merciless, Menacing Masked Meanie

6. The Adventures Of Philbert Desenex

7. Wonder Wart-Hog Meets The Merangsters
name: Wonder Wart-Hog Meets Super-Fool

volume.name: Not Only The Best of Wonder Wart-Hog

description: Venus wants Buddy to quit asking her to "make puppies." Buddy wants Winston's help wooing Venus. Winston wants Guy's respect. Guy wants Dolly's job. Dolly wants to know the meaning of it all. Nobody knows what Fiddler really wants, not even Fiddler. But mostly, these sled dogs just want to run. Sounds simple? It should be, but even dogs have their problems. From Colbert Report writer Glenn Eichler comes a postmodern tale of heroism on the tundra, epic romance, and yellow snow.
name: Sled Dogs with Issues

description: In 1804, Meriwether Lewis and William Clark set out on one of the greatest adventures this nation has ever known. Their mission was to follow the Missouri river from Pittsburgh all the way west to the Pacific Ocean. Appointed and funded by President Jefferson himself, well-staffed, lavishly equipped, and led by a cadre of experts (including the famous Sacajawea), the expedition was considered a success almost before it had begun. There was only one problem: Everything.
name: GN

description:
Atomic Robo faces an invasion from the Vampire Dimension, finds a giant kaiju monster attack in the heart of Tokyo, detours to the South Pacific to battle wits with Dr. Dinosaur, then comes face-to-face with his newest enemy: his oldest enemy!

Collects Atomic Robo: Revenge Of The Vampire Dimension #1-4.
name: Volume Four

description: Neal Barton just wants to read in peace. Unluckly for him, some local Christian activists are trying to get his favorite fantasy series banned from the Americus Public Library. Something has to be done, and it looks like quiet, shy Neal is going to have to do it. With youth services librarian Charlotte Murphy at his back, Neal finds himself leading the charge to defend the fantasy series that makes his life worth living.
name: GN

description: In "I Love Him To Pieces," can love survive the zombie apocalypse? Maybe Dicey's first chance at a real relationship was dead from the start. Her idea of a study session includes sleeping in the sun, and his idea of a good game involves dungeons and dice. But opposites start attracting when they're assigned to be partners in a class project. Now an outbreak of a weird infection - it eats your brains and leaves you hungry for more - might not mean just the end of their first date. It might mean the end of everything!
name: I Love Him to Pieces!

description:
1. Introduction

2. When Good Bombs Happen to Bad People

3. More Women, More Children, More Quickly
name: Airpower through Victory

person_credits.name: Joe Sacco
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Tom Stone stepped into Seward High and Maria McBride's life like a bolt of lightning. He's the perfect guy for Maria - nice, smart, and well-built. There's just one problem: his family. Tom's father is the town's new funeral director, and business is booming. The bodies are piling up thick and fast in Persephone Falls, Alaska, so Dr. Stone keeps Tom up late at night working in the funeral home. And it's clear that Dr. Stone and his creepy assistant, Graves, don't want Maria around. When Tom refuses to stand up to his father, Maria begins to stitch together the clues - and finds out that the Stones are into recycling in ways she never could have imagined!
name: Made For Each Other!
